is about a 1.1% increase

13
00:00:47,324 --> 00:00:49,277
in the global population each year,

14
00:00:49,277 --> 00:00:53,165
and the population will double 
every sixty years at current rates.

15
00:00:54,090 --> 00:00:57,817
One useful way to classify diseases
was was proposed by the authors

16
00:00:57,817 --> 00:01:01,196
of the 1972 classic book 
“Drawers of Water”.

17
00:01:01,196 --> 00:01:04,152
According to environmental 
transmission pathways

18
00:01:04,152 --> 00:01:09,266
this so called “Bradley Classification” 
includes four types: water-borne,

19
00:01:09,266 --> 00:01:13,016
water-washed, water-based
and water-related diseases.

20
00:01:14,264 --> 00:01:18,559
Now some of those 55 million deaths 
per year are caused, at least in part

21
00:01:18,559 --> 00:01:21,110
by unsafe water, sanitation and hygiene.

22
00:01:21,221 --> 00:01:24,499
And we can think about different ways
to classify those diseases.

23
00:01:24,807 --> 00:01:27,508
First, we can talk about 
the water-borne diseases

24
00:01:27,508 --> 00:01:31,192
which are diseases caused 
by actually drinking, ingesting water

25
00:01:31,192 --> 00:01:32,965
that has some pathogens in it.

26
00:01:33,235 --> 00:01:36,808
These include the diarrheal diseases 
caused by different pathogens:

27
00:01:36,808 --> 00:01:39,982
Rotavirus, Cholera, 
Shigella or Cyptosporidium

28
00:01:40,447 --> 00:01:42,799
but also Hepatitis A and E

29
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:46,083
and even Polio can be transmitted 
through drinking water.

30
00:01:46,372 --> 00:01:48,265
For any of these water-borne diseases

31
00:01:48,265 --> 00:01:53,491
an intervention to reduce the disease then
could involve improving the water quality.

32
00:01:55,046 --> 00:01:58,470
Next we have the water-washed diseases
which are caused by poor hygiene

33
00:01:58,470 --> 00:02:01,830
due to lack of water 
rather than by direct ingestion.

34
00:02:02,359 --> 00:02:04,757
Most water-borne diseases 
are also water-washed

35
00:02:04,757 --> 00:02:06,840
because they can be transmitted 
through hands

36
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:09,026
and contact with other surfaces.

37
00:02:09,456 --> 00:02:13,291
Trachoma is the leading cause 
of preventable blindness globally

38
00:02:13,291 --> 00:02:17,313
and is transmitted by flies 
which land on people's faces.

39
00:02:17,890 --> 00:02:21,635
And acute respiratory infections 
are also transmitted through contact

40
00:02:21,635 --> 00:02:24,558
with pathogens on hands 
and other surfaces.

41
00:02:25,853 --> 00:02:27,898
